Ask any motivational speaker what they like least about their job, and they will tell you it's the travel. Because of my international client base, heading to JFK is part of virtually every assignment I have. I mostly fly first class. In fact, it's a clause in my contract ??? one that I rarely negotiate. I don't fly first class because I am a snob or because I'm temperamental and require lots of pampering. I fly up front because it makes good business sense.
